# Redirect legacy /posts/* URLs to new /blog/* structure
/posts                    /blog              301
/posts/                   /blog              301
/posts/page/*             /blog              301

# Legacy template post-N slugs (placeholder content was removed 2026-05-02).
# 410 = Gone — tells crawlers these URLs are intentionally retired and should
# be deindexed without retry. Switch back to a 301 to /blog if you ever want
# to gracefully forward stale traffic instead of removing the URLs entirely.
/blog/post-1              /blog              410
/blog/post-2              /blog              410
/blog/post-3              /blog              410
/blog/post-4              /blog              410
/blog/post-5              /blog              410
/blog/post-6              /blog              410
/blog/post-7              /blog              410
/blog/post-8              /blog              410
/blog/post-9              /blog              410
/blog/post-10             /blog              410
/posts/post-*             /blog              410
/posts/*                  /blog/:splat       301

# Journal entries are PIN-encrypted and only addressable via the SPA's
# `#/<slug>` hash routes. Direct .md URL hits (stale links, copy-paste,
# crawlers) bounce to the gate instead of 404'ing. The SPA's link rewriter
# handles in-app navigation; this is defense-in-depth for everything else.
/docs/journal/*.md        /docs/journal/     302
